DIRECTIONS:
First, check whether the student's revision email overlaps in content with the checklists
provided by other students. If there is such an overlap, say so briefly, in a sentence or so.

Next, check whether the student's revision email overlaps in content with the list of AI
suggestions. If there is any overlap, identify it and point out what parts of the response
are original -- that is, present neither in the checklists nor in the AI response.

Finally, evaluate the advice provided in the student email for consistency with what is
known about using operant conditioning to treat sleep refusal and with what is known about
effective ways to improve adherence to an intervention, focusing on whether the proposed
plan is sound and effective.
