<HH> ============= Screen: Updated plan ========================= </HH>

<Vertical id="fba3_updated_plan">
<Markdown>
## Updated Behavior Modification Plan

Based on your selected modifications, here is the updated plan:
</Markdown>

<LLMFeedback id="fba3_updated_plan_response" render="markdown" />

<ActionButton id="fba3_generate_plan_btn" label="Generate Updated Plan">
<LLMAction id="fba3_generate_plan_action" target="fba3_updated_plan_response"><![CDATA[
You are helping a group of psychology students update a behavior modification plan for a child named Johnny who has escape-maintained bedtime behavior. His babysitter has been struggling with adherence to the original plan.

Here is the ORIGINAL escape-focused behavior modification plan:

**Target Behavior:** Johnny does not go to bed on time
**Function of Behavior:** Escape
**Behavior Goal:** Johnny will go to bed on time when told, without running away, for 4 out of 5 bedtimes over a 2-week period

**Antecedent Strategies:**
- Create a predictable bedtime routine with a visual schedule
- Use a timer to signal when each routine step begins and ends
- Give 10-minute and 5-minute advance warnings
- Incorporate a brief preferred activity into the routine
- Allow limited choices within the routine

**Consequence Strategies:**
- Provide positive reinforcement (sticker chart, praise) for on-time bedtime
- Ignore escape behaviors — do not chase or engage
- Use a "bedtime pass" for one approved brief delay per night
- Provide brief positive attention when Johnny stays in bed

**Data Collection:**
- Track whether Johnny goes to bed on time each night for 2 weeks
- Note any modifications or deviations from the plan

The student selected these modifications to improve the babysitter's adherence:
]]>
<Ref id="fba3_ref_modifications" target="fba3_modification_choices" />
<![CDATA[
The student's reasoning for choosing these modifications:
]]>
<Ref id="fba3_ref_mod_explanation" target="fba3_modification_explanation" />
<![CDATA[
Now generate an UPDATED plan that:
1. Keeps all the original antecedent and consequence strategies
2. Incorporates the student's selected modifications as a new "Adherence Supports" section
3. Updates the Data Collection section to include fidelity tracking
4. Uses clear Markdown formatting with bold headers and bullet points
5. Is specific and actionable — tailor the adherence supports to Johnny's bedtime scenario
6. Keeps the plan concise (no more than ~300 words)

Format the plan with these sections:
- Target Behavior / Function / Goal (brief header)
- Antecedent Strategies
- Consequence Strategies
- New Adherence Supports (based on student's selections)
- Data Collection
]]></LLMAction>
</ActionButton>
