<Vertical id="fba3_progress_graph_2">
<Markdown>
## Progress Monitoring: Week 3–4

After implementing the modifications, Annie's roommate tracked another 5 sessions:
</Markdown>
<ObservablePlot id="fba3_week3_chart" title="Johnny's Bedtimes (Week 3–4)" format="js"><![CDATA[
const data = [
  { date: "9/19", bedtimeIndex: 0 },
  { date: "9/20", bedtimeIndex: 1 },
  { date: "9/24", bedtimeIndex: 0 },
  { date: "9/25", bedtimeIndex: 0 },
  { date: "9/26", bedtimeIndex: 0 }
];

function formatBedtimeLabel(index) {
  const labels = {
    "-0.25": "7:45 PM",
    0: "8:00 PM",
    1: "8:30 PM",
    2: "9:00 PM",
    "2.25": "9:15 PM"
  };
  return labels[index] ?? `${index}`;
}

return Plot.plot({
  width: 680,
  height: 300,
  marginLeft: 72,
  marginBottom: 48,
  marks: [
    Plot.lineY(data, {
      x: "date",
      y: "bedtimeIndex",
      stroke: "#111827",
      curve: "linear",
      strokeWidth: 3,
      clip: false
    }),
    Plot.dot(data, {
      x: "date",
      y: "bedtimeIndex",
      stroke: "#111827",
      fill: "#111827",
      r: 4,
      clip: false
    })
  ],
  x: {
    label: "Date",
    ticks: data.map((d) => d.date)
  },
  y: {
    label: "Bedtime",
    domain: [-0.25, 2.25],
    ticks: [0, 1, 2],
    tickFormat: formatBedtimeLabel
  }
});
]]></ObservablePlot>
<Markdown>
**The modified intervention was a success!**

Annie's roommate reports that with the simplified checklist and phone reminders, she was able to follow the plan much more consistently. Johnny went to bed on time in **4 out of 5** sessions — a big improvement from Week 1–2.
</Markdown>
</Vertical>
